-- fibonacci-crystal.cell: compute fibonacci, verify by recurrence
-- Oracle: fib(n) = fib(n-1) + fib(n-2), not by hard-coding the answer

вҠў fib
  given n вүЎ 10
  yield result

  вҲҙ Compute the В«nВ»th Fibonacci number.
    fib(0)=0, fib(1)=1, fib(n)=fib(n-1)+fib(n-2).

вҠў fib-prev
  given n вүЎ 9
  yield result

  вҲҙ Compute the В«nВ»th Fibonacci number.
    fib(0)=0, fib(1)=1, fib(n)=fib(n-1)+fib(n-2).

вҠў fib-prev2
  given n вүЎ 8
  yield result

  вҲҙ Compute the В«nВ»th Fibonacci number.
    fib(0)=0, fib(1)=1, fib(n)=fib(n-1)+fib(n-2).

вҠў verify-recurrence
  given fibвҶ’result
  given fib-prevвҶ’result as prev
  given fib-prev2вҶ’result as prev2
  yield holds

  вҠў= holds вҶҗ fibвҶ’result = fib-prevвҶ’result + fib-prev2вҶ’result

  вҠЁ holds = true

вҠў crystallize
  given В§fib
  given verify-recurrenceвҶ’holds where holds = true
  yield В§fib', is-faithful

  вҲҙ Read В«В§fibВ». It computes Fibonacci numbers.
    Write a вҠў= expression using Cell primitives.

вҠў verify-crystal
  given В§fib'
  given crystallizeвҶ’is-faithful
  yield approved

  вҲҙ Does В«В§fib'В» produce a deterministic computation?

  вҠЁ if approved and crystallizeвҶ’is-faithful then В§fib' may replace В§fib
